      "writtenOn": "2026-03-13T06:12:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "While the IPMI specification is flexible, this change aligns with Linux and POSIX standards used in OpenBMC.\nStarting a username with a number can cause ambiguity with User IDs (UIDs) in system commands (like chown). Restricting the first character to an alphabetical letter ensures compatibility with the underlying operating system and prevents potential errors during user management.",
